	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Intentional PPU hum...</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes, I used a Y cable to split the video signal to make the video I posted. I wouldn't suggest that this will work in all cases (probably depends a lot on the video and audio inputs you connect to), but it was good enough in my particular case to make that recording. If you were doing it properly you'd want an active splitter that can buffer the two outputs, not just a passive Y cable.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
