	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>lidnariq</b> [ Mon Nov 11, 2013 6:14 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Intentional PPU hum...</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You're basically not going to be able to hear any difference as to where things are on the left or right side of the screen; your ears can't hear at those frequencies. All-in-all, it'll sound like a bunch of overtones of 60.1Hz, at varying strengths, and there will a strong correlation with total screen brightness and loudness.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


